        <p>For each host-based tool, the ROC curves (left) and Precision-Recall curves (right) based on the test dataset are presented for the 5 best classifiers of each type and compared to the “naive” approach, i.e., best hit based on the raw score. FPR, false positive rate; PPV, positive predictive value; TPR, true positive rate. The 1-to-1 line is indicated as a dashed black line on the ROC curves. Random forest classifiers were only evaluated for Blast and CRISPR approaches. Source data are available in <xref rid="pbio.3002083.s021" ref-type="supplementary-material">S1 Data</xref> (Source data 5).</p>
