        <p>The number of correct host predictions was evaluated for 3 different score cutoffs corresponding to 20%, 10%, and 5% estimated FDR (false discovery rate). Input viruses were classified into 5 categories (x-axis) based on their AAI (average amino acid identity) to the closest reference phage genome. The number of correct host predictions is indicated for each iPHoP classifier (see <xref rid="pbio.3002083.g003" ref-type="fig">Fig 3A</xref>) and for the composite score considering all classifiers (“Final iPHoP prediction”). Source data are available in <xref rid="pbio.3002083.s021" ref-type="supplementary-material">S1 Data</xref> (Source data 3).</p>
